dct_description_sm: U.S. Department of the Interior Geological Survey map of the Ramsey quadrangle in New York and north-eastern New Jersey. The New York portion is left blank as it is already depicted in the Ramapo quadrangle map. Major highways and significant destinations outside of map area are shown in red.
Small sections missing and five strips of adhesive tape are visible along the top.
